Pikachu

Evolves At 5

Static

Passive Ability

Upon receiving damage: paralyzes all nearby opposing Pokémon (30s CD).

Paralysis from Static decreases opposing Pokémon movement speed by 30% and reduces auto attack speed by a flat 10% for 2s.

Surge Surfer

Passive Ability

Alolan Raichu can use basic attacks while moving.

After using a move or a boosted attack: dashes in the direction of movement.

Attack - Pikachu

Auto Attack

Becomes a boosted attack with every third attack, dealing increased damage and paralyzing the opposing Pokémon hit.

Paralysis from Pikachu's boosted attacks decreases opposing Pokémon movement speed by 30% and reduces auto attack speed by a flat 10% for 2s.

Attack - Raichu

Auto Attack

After hitting 4 basic attacks or moves, the next basic attack becomes a boosted attack. Boosted attacks release electricity at the target that can chain to other nearby opposing Pokémon, dealing increased damage to up to 5 opposing Pokémon.

72% SpA + 0 x (Level - 1) + 80

93.6% SpA + 0 x (Level - 1) + 104

Thunder Shock

Move 1

5.00s Sure Hit

Releases electricity at the designated opposing Pokémon; damaging opposing Pokémon in the area of effect and paralyzing those hit.

Paralysis from this move decreases opposing Pokémon movement speed by 30% and reduces auto attack speed by a flat 10% for 2s.

90% SpA + 0 x (Level - 1) + 240

Thunder Shock Upgrade Choices

Stored Power

4.50s Buff

Increases auto attack speed by 50% and empowers the next 6 auto attacks for 5s.

Each empowered auto attack also launches a star-shaped electric blast at the target, dealing additional damage. This move goes on cooldown after all 6 electric blasts have been launched or after 5s.

80% SpA + 0 x (Level - 1) + 88

The electric blasts also decrease the target's Sp. Def by 10% for 3s (up to 3 times; maximum 30%).

Electro Ball

6.00s Area

Hurls an electric orb toward the designated location, where it remains for up to 30s if it doesn't hit an opposing Pokémon on the way. When an electric orb and an opposing Pokémon touch; the orb releases its electricity and damages nearby opposing Pokémon.

A maximum of 2 uses can be kept in reserve, with a 0.5s cooldown between uses. A maximum of 3 orbs can be on the map at a given time.

176% SpA + 0 x (Level - 1) + 335

193.6% SpA + 0 x (Level - 1) + 368

Deals damage every 0.5s over 3.5s (8 times) to opposing Pokémon hit by this move.

7.7% SpA + 0 x (Level - 1) + 18

Thunder Wave

Move 2

9.00s Hindrance

Discharges a weak jolt of electricity in the designated direction; damaging nearby opposing Pokémon and paralyzing those hit.

Paralysis from this move decreases opposing Pokémon movement speed by 30% and reduces auto attack speed by a flat 10% for 2s.

108% SpA + 0 x (Level - 1) + 300

Thunder Wave Upgrade Choices

Thunderbolt

6.00s Hindrance

Channels for 0.5s then releases a strong electric blast in the designated direction, damaging opposing Pokémon in the area of effect, and paralyzing them when it hits. Paralysis from this move decreases opposing Pokémon movement speed by 30% and reduces auto attack speed by a flat 10% for 1s.

If this move hits an electric orb created by Electro Ball; the orb releases its electricity, dealing increased damage to nearby opposing Pokémon.

160% SpA + 0 x (Level - 1) + 380

Immobilizes opposing Pokémon hit for 1s instead of paralyzing them.

Psychic

9.00s Area

Releases a strong telekinetic force in the designated area, damage opposing Pokémon in the area of effect and applying a debuff which decreases their movement speed by 23% for 3s when it hits. If the user hits debuffed opposing Pokémon with an auto attack, it deals additional damage.

If this move hits an electric orb created by Electro Ball; the orb is pulled to the center of this move's area of effect. This does not extend the duration the electric orb remains.

102.4% SpA + 0 x (Level - 1) + 240

16% SpA + 0 x (Level - 1) + 40

Creates a damage-over-time area of effect, damaging opposing Pokémon inside the area every 0.5s over 2s (up to 5 times).

10.24% SpA + 0 x (Level - 1) + 24

Thunderstorm Aerial

Unite Move

112s 100000 Area

Unlocks at level 9

Creates a star-shaped zone of electricity in the designated area for 4s, damaging opposing Pokémon in the area of effect when created, then damaging opposing Pokémon over time (up to 5 times) and decreasing their movement speed by 60% while in the zone.

If the user hits an opposing Pokémon that is in the zone with an auto attack, the next basic attack becomes a boosted attack.

168% SpA + 0 x (Level - 1) + 400

33.6% SpA + 0 x (Level - 1) + 80

Unite Buffs (6s duration):

30% Movement Speed, 35% Attack Speed, 20% Max HP Shield
